replies.body:
@Riot Galetta; The community loves skins on newer champions because new champions mean (As the receiver) Not much variety outside of game-play kit experience will be added. So to finally invite at least 3 new skins within several months time since release no matter how small, i personally see it as worth it. But as an artist, i know better. Good art takes time, and the people working at riot should cherish it as much as possible before nearing possible deadlines. I really would love it for y'all to keep taking your time to make these wonderful works of art, but we all know people are impatient and the community can be very picky.

Personally the Ekko skin is bad simply because in my opinion the theme doesn't fit him as well as others. But you know what? Y'all made a release skin and with that to compare to, i have something to fall back on and enjoy regardless, still throwing money at the screen but because you made room for variety. Plz be sure to let the people who put the time and hard work into making these concepts come to life did an incredible job!

Cheers!
